src: 2. 安全理事会第1704（2006）号决议第4段批准东帝汶综合团的授权，规定了广泛的任务，包括向政府和有关机构提供支助，以巩固稳定，加强民主施政的文化；协助东帝汶各利益攸关方进行政治对话，在2007年总统选举和议会选举的所有方面向东帝汶提供支助；支持国防军和国防部，支持东帝汶国家警察和内务部，包括恢复和维持东帝汶的公共安全和援助国家警察和内务部的培训、体制发展和加强工作；促进人权、正义与和解（包括针对妇女和儿童），并通过完成对1999年东帝汶严重侵犯人权行为尚未结案案件的调查这样做；支持体制能力建设、治理和发展；人道主义支助；支持促进两性平等和增强妇女能力；与联合国各机构、基金和方案及所有有关合作伙伴，包括国际金融机构和捐助者，对冲突后建设和平与能力建设的双边和多边援助开展合作和协调；向东帝汶人民提供客观和准确的信息，特别是关于即将举行的2007年选举的信息，同时增进他们对东帝汶综合团工作的了解，协助地方媒体建立能力；协同国际安全部队，确保联合国人员和有关人员的安全和行动自由，保护联合国人员、设施、装置和设备和人道主义资产。
true_meaning: In paragraph 4 of its resolution 1704 (2006), the Security Council approved the mandate of UNMIT, setting out a broad range of tasks related to support for the Government of Timor-Leste and relevant institutions in consolidating stability, enhancing a culture of democratic governance and facilitating political dialogue among Timorese stakeholders; support for Timor-Leste in all aspects of the 2007 presidential and parliamentary electoral process; support to the national armed forces and the Ministry of Defence; support to the Timorese national police (PNLT) and the Ministry of Interior, including in the restoration and maintenance of public security in Timor-Leste and assistance in the training, institutional development and strengthening of PNTL and the Ministry of Interior; the promotion of human rights, justice and reconciliation, including for women and children, and through the completion of investigations into outstanding serious human rights violations committed in the country in 1999; support in institutional capacity-building, governance and development; humanitarian support; support in the promotion of gender equality and the empowerment of women; cooperation and coordination with United Nations agencies, funds and programmes and relevant partners, including the international financial institutions and donors, of bilateral and multilateral assistance to Timor-Leste in post-conflict peacebuilding and capacity-building; the provision of objective and accurate information to the Timorese people, in particular, on the forthcoming 2007 elections, and UNMIT activities, as well as assistance in building local media capacity; ensuring, in coordination with the international security forces, the security and freedom of movement of United Nations and associated personnel, and the protection of United Nations personnel, facilities, installations and equipment and humanitarian assets.
predicted: - The Security Council, in its resolution 1704 (2006), paragraph 4, authorized the Special Representative of the Secretary-General for Timor-Leste, with a broad mandate, including providing assistance to the Government and relevant institutions to consolidate stability and strengthen democratic governance; assisting the people of Timor-Leste in all aspects of the 2007 presidential and parliamentary elections; supporting the Timor-Leste Defence Forces and the Ministry of Defence, supporting the Timor-Leste National Police and the Ministry of Internal Affairs, including restoring and maintaining public safety and assisting in the training, institutional development and capacity-building of the National Police and the Ministry of Internal Affairs; promoting human rights, justice and reconciliation (including for women and children) and doing so by completing the investigation of the serious human rights violations that occurred in Timor-Leste in 1999; supporting capacity-building, governance and development; humanitarian assistance; supporting the promotion of gender equality and the empowerment of women; cooperating and coordinating with the United Nations agencies, funds and programmes and all relevant partners, including international financial institutions and donors, on bilateral and multilateral assistance for post-conflict peace-building and capacity-building; providing the people of Timor-Leste with objective and accurate information, in particular about the upcoming 2007 elections, while increasing their understanding of the work of the Special Representative of the Secretary-General, assisting in the development of the capacity of local media; coordinating with international security forces to ensure the safety and freedom of action of United Nations personnel and relevant personnel, protecting United Nations personnel, facilities, equipment and assets and humanitarian assets.

true_meaning: The main reasons for the approach of the UNCITRAL Secured Transactions Guide with respect to outright transfers of receivables are: (i) the need to have a comprehensive set of priority rules where there are multiple assignments of the same receivables by the same assignor mainly based on registration (with the exception of receivables embodied in negotiable instruments with respect to which possession gives a superior security right); (ii) the need to address a priority conflict between an assignment by way of security, an outright assignment and the creation of a security right in a receivable; and (iii) the difficulty of third parties to determine whether an assignment is by way of security, an outright assignment or a transaction creating a security right in a receivable.
